The course is aimed at preparing the students for the William C. Vis international moot court competition. During the course the students solve a complex international trade law case, learn the basic rules of CISG and get familiarised with the most common instruments on iternational arbitration. During the first part of the competition the students write written memoranda for claimant and respondent.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The general goal  of the course is to provide intensive training on international commercial law and arbitration for resolution of international business disputes through the participation in William C.Vis International Commercial Arbitration Moot.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students gain skills to apply international commerical law to a concrete problem of a client and prepare the case (incl. writing memoranda) within the framework of the alternative dispute resolution.
